oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Interior view with wicker furniture
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Black and white photograph of the interior of the Croft house in Havana, Cuba, showing a fainting couch and wicker chair. Visible in the background are a side table, mirror, stool, and a doorway with shutters which leads outside.
This is the second of two houses the Crofts owned in Havana, located at 19 and F streets in Vedado. The first house was located at 26 F Street, Vedado.
